indarel/replic/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">28</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":28,\"repo\":\"vindarel/replic\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - helpers to turn existing code into a readline application, with a focus on defining the completion of the commands' arguments. Also comes as a ready to use executable, that transforms a user's lispy init file into readline commands. <a href=\"https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT\">MIT</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-14T15:38:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CodyReichert/awesome-cl","categoryHTML":"<h2>Readline, ncurses and other graphical helpers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vindarel/cl-ansi-term\">cl-ansi-term</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vindarel/cl-ansi-term\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">23</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":23,\"repo\":\"vindarel/cl-ansi-term\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - print\ncolorized text, horizontal lines, progress bars, (un)ordered lists\nand tables on ANSI-compliant terminals. <a href=\"http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html\">GPL3</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-14T15:38:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CodyReichert/awesome-cl","categoryHTML":"<h2>Shells, shells interfaces</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/fukamachi/shelly\">Shelly</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/fukamachi/shelly\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">65</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":65,\"repo\":\"fukamachi/shelly\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - execute Common Lisp\nfunctions like a shell command, without the need to write a command\nline arguments parser. And it also can be used as a Make-like\nbuild-tool. <a href=\"https://directory.fsf.org/wiki?title=License:FreeBSD\">FreeBSD</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-14T15:38:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CodyReichert/awesome-cl","categoryHTML":"<h2>System administration</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cl-adams/adams\">Adams</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cl-adams/adams\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">157</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":157,\"repo\":\"cl-adams/adams\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - UNIX system administration in Common Lisp. Not unlike Ansible, Chef or Puppet. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISC_license\">ISC</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-14T15:38:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CodyReichert/awesome-cl","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other scripting utilities</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wadehennessey/wcl\">WCL</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wadehennessey/wcl\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">69</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":69,\"repo\":\"wadehennessey/wcl\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> [staled] - allow hundreds of Lisp</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-14T15:38:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"LappleApple/awesome-leading-and-managing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Contents</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/LappleApple/awesome-leading-and-managing/blob/master/Media-Blogs-Newsletters-Podcasts.md\">Media: Blogs, Newsletters, Podcasts</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-14T13:55:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"LappleApple/awesome-leading-and-managing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Contents</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/LappleApple/awesome-leading-and-managing/blob/master/The-CTO-role.md\">The CTO Role</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-14T13:54:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-nodejs","categoryHTML":"<h2>Packages</h2><h3>Miscellane